#
# Summary
#


My overall feeling with this document, is that things are simple & working \ô/


What I liked especially:

 - I was immediately directed to a test sigsum log where I can experiment
 - I have files that I can inspect and modify to easily test things
 - I can see what is happening, because what matters to me is:

    - where are the bytes being read, can you show them to me?
    - where are the bytes being written, can you show them to me?
    - where is the network interaction happening?


What I would have liked:

 - some "--verbose" verbose flag that makes the tools very noisy

    - maybe add it and only mention its existence at the start?
    - tools being silent when my attention is not needed is good

    - however, when I feel dumb, I like having an option to say

        "explain to me what you are doing, reading, writing, etc"

            +especially what other computers I am talking to
            +what unexpected branches I am triggering (*.proof already exists)

    - this is close but not exactly "--diagnostics=info" or debug

        as a user that will never look at sigsum implementation, I want a way
        to say to my machine "tell me the work you are doing" so it becomes
        easier to me to grasp what the tool is doing, w-o looking at the docs

